snippet.textDisplay:
Yes, a man can be blinded by greed and power, he can do bad things and be called evil but it's who we are at the end that really matters. Todoroki understands that endeavour feels bad for the things he's done in the past and he's trying to be a hero his children can be proud of.
This is why I prefer endeavour to all might. The man who falls and gets back up is greater than the man who never fell.
